# Context 
You are provided with a website that let's you initiate the smart contract provided in the challenge.sol file. This was my initiated contract : https://ropsten.etherscan.io/address/0x17cd82538e5d9a466c391a6af90414e7f02807ba 
You are prompted to empty the funds of the contract. 

This is enough info to solve the challenge. 

# Solving 

There are multiple ways to solve this. The way I did it was by loading the contract on the Remix IDE and then launching it on my contract adress. Once you've done that, you'll see that all the functions (or almost) require you to be the contract owner. An the function to change owner needs a private key.  
By exploring a bit the ethereum blockchain, you discover that this the contract that initiates your contract : https://ropsten.etherscan.io/address/0x9196432d40387c7b6c05f9c1cbbdcd2f2b034c3a#code
Decompile the Bytecode. 
You'll see this line in the code :       
            code: , 0x64b461af1f85090f9bd2670d8ec675afd720b165831d62996dba8c703507676a

This string at the end looks familiar : 0x64b461af1f85090f9bd2670d8ec675afd720b165831d62996dba8c703507676a  
It fits the lenght of your necessary key. It is in fact the key for the contract (It was used as input to create the contract, thats why you see it in the blockchain). 
Put it in the change_owner() function and then use the empty_funds() function
